entries.content: Objections are not rejections but indicators of the need for more information or commitment.
entries.notes: Implied through frustration with lack of personal investment, suggesting objections signal unreadiness, not outright rejection.

entries.content: "I'd love to work with you, I've just got to see if my boss will pay" is an objection that qualifies the prospect out due to lack of personal commitment.
entries.notes: Demonstrates treating objections as signals of prospect's mindset rather than rejection.

focus_area: Objection Mindset: Objections = info requests, not rejections
